The paper presents a visual place recognition system that uses a pre-trained Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture to encode images of places. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the system encodes semantic and spatial information in the form of CNN features, which could also relate to Robotics (cs.RO) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which could indicate a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
